    await authClient.signIn.social(
      {
        provider: provider,
      },
      {
        onSuccess: (ctx) => {
          console.log(
            "authtoken in ctx of socialSignIn:",
            ctx.response.headers.get("set-auth-token"),
          );
          navigate("/");
        },
        //...
      },
    );
  }

//...
```

The statement 
```ts
console.log(
            "authtoken in ctx of socialSignIn:",
            ctx.response.headers.get("set-auth-token"),
          );
```

runs instantly when `socialSignIn("google")` is called after clicking the signin button and I see the log statement. but this doesn't run after i "choose an account" -> "continue" and come back to main dashboard. when am i supposed to get the bearer token in social signin?

